	     <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform"><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=162565"><span id="Scholar">LadyTrouble</span></a><br /><b><span id="Scholar">Scholar</span></b><br /><span id="notbold">65 posts<br /><span id="notbold">Score:</span> Decent [3.11]</td><td valign=top class="mform" width="100%"><p>Untrue<br/><br/>The way multiple procs work, is with each swing, a roll is thrown for each proc.&nbsp;&nbsp;However, only one proc can activate per swing.  So, you will never have more than one proc per swing, but you have a greater chance for a proc going off per swing.  So, as a pally, if you have a spell proc, your fiery defender, and a nice DD aug in it, You have a 3 times greater chance of your weapon procing per swing.</p>&nbsp;<br /><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br />Hunt Well and Be Safe!</td></tr>
